        <q>Page 28, line 43, at end insert ("and any charges imposed shall be reasonable").</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0576P0-01684'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0576P0_19961126_GCR_79' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: The purpose of Amendments Nos. 65 and 66 is that there should be an overriding requirement that charges imposed are reasonable, and that there should be an appeals procedure against the level of charges. Recommendation 98 of the Donaldson Report calls for,
        <q>charges sufficient, but not more than is required".</q>
      </p>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_74gc' title='Col. 74GC &mdash; HL Deb 26 November 1996 vol 576 c74GC' name='column_74gc' href='#column_74gc' rel='bookmark'>74GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0576P0-01685'>
